{
  "texts": [
    "Since deterministic short-term WPP is most frequently studied, we consider the wind turbine power output prediction with horizons ranging from 10 to 60 min in this computational experiment.",
    "Meanwhile, processed data are divided into the training set, validation set, and test set respectively with a 0.6:0.2:0.2 split ratio.",
    "The commonly considered RMSE metric is employed to evaluate the WPP performance of developed models.",
    "An extended set of promising DL models including DLinear, Informer, Transformer, CNN, LSTM, GRU and DNN are considered in this further computational experiment based on recent studies (Zhou et al. 2022a, b; Zhou et al. 2021; Zeng et al.2023).",
    "Results of our computational experiments are reported in Table 10."
  ]
}